Question :- 2

Compare using a TextFormField inside a Form widget with a GlobalKey versus writing
manual validation logic inside setState. In this checkout context, what specific advantage does
the Form widget approach offer, and when might manual validation still be the better choice?


Ans :- 

Using a TextFormField inside a Form widget with a GlobalKey is the recommended approach for validating a shipping address form because it provides a built-in,organized, and reusable validation system. 
Each TextFormField has its own validator function, and calling formKey.currentState!.validate() checks all fields at once before allowing checkout.

Form Widget with GlobalKey : -

-> Uses built-in validation through validator.
-> Validates all fields with a single call (validate()).
-> Displays error messages automatically below each field.
-> Keeps the code clean, readable, and easy to maintain.
-> Prevents checkout until all required fields (street address and 6-digit pincode) are valid.

Manual Validation with setState : -

-> Validation logic is written manually inside setState().
-> The developer must check each field, update error messages, and manage the UI.
-> Requires more code and is harder to maintain for larger forms.
